<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-21T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-21T20:00:00-05:00" n="472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/7842: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Des Portes</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-21T21:00:00-04:00">July 21,
                                    1942—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>283. For Holt. Your 251, July 20. Rubber Reserve, Board of Economic
                            Warfare and Department believe that you have been exceptionally
                            successful in obtaining agreement on basis outlined, and you are
                            authorized to sign an agreement on this basis. Please advise when
                            signature completed so that a press release may be issued and also
                            forward as soon as possible copies of signed agreement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>